main event: Mr. and Mrs. Smith from Bethel, Vermont, reported observing two unidentified flying objects in the sky on January 8, 1965.
interesting points: The first object was round, reddish-orange and pulsating, observed moving slowly from east to west at an estimated altitude of 2000 feet., A second similar object was spotted shortly after at a higher altitude., The objects appeared to be metallic and were in view for approximately 10 to 15 minutes., Witnesses reported no sound associated with the objects., The observers are considered reliable citizens of the community.
witness description: Mr. Donald Smith and Mrs. Jean Smith, reliable citizens of Bethel, Vermont.
